#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.56"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.56:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.56:0.2"
msgid "6. Upayavagga"
msgstr "6. Involvement"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 56. Upādānaparipavattasutta → upadānam parivaṭṭam (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.56:0.3"
msgid "56. Upādānaparipavattasutta"
msgstr "56. Perspectives"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.59"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.56:1.2"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, upādānakkhandhā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five grasping aggregates."

msgctxt "sn22.56:1.3"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:1.4"
msgid ""
"Rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"The grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.56:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ime pañcupādānakkhandhe catuparivaṭṭaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake "
"sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ "
"sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"As long as I didn’t truly understand these five grasping aggregates from "
"four perspectives, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this "
"world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics "
"and brahmins, its gods and humans."

msgctxt "sn22.56:1.6"
msgid ""
"Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ime pañcupādānakkhandhe catuparivaṭṭaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke … pe …"
msgstr ""
"But when I did truly understand these five grasping aggregates from four "
"perspectives, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with "
"its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and "
"brahmins, its gods and humans."

msgctxt "sn22.56:1.7"
msgid "sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca catuparivaṭṭaṃ?"
msgstr "And how are there four perspectives?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:2.2"
msgid ""
"Rūpaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, rūpasamudayaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, rūpanirodhaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, "
"rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"I directly knew form, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads "
"to its cessation."

msgctxt "sn22.56:2.3"
msgid "vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "I directly knew feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.56:2.4"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.56:2.5"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.56:2.6"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, viññāṇasamudayaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, viññāṇanirodhaṃ "
"abbhaññāsiṃ, viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its "
"cessation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is form?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:3.2"
msgid "Cattāro ca mahābhūtā catunnañca mahābhūtānaṃ upādāya rūpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The four primary elements, and form derived from the four primary elements."

msgctxt "sn22.56:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, rūpaṃ."
msgstr "This is called form."

msgctxt "sn22.56:3.4"
msgid "Āhārasamudayā rūpasamudayo;"
msgstr "Form originates from food."

msgctxt "sn22.56:3.5"
msgid "āhāranirodhā rūpanirodho."
msgstr "When food ceases, form ceases."

msgctxt "sn22.56:3.6"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo rūpanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of form is simply this noble "
"eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "sn22.56:3.7"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ rūpaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"rūpasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ rūpanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya rūpassa nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya "
"paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā."
msgstr ""
"Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known form in this way—and its "
"origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation—and are "
"practicing for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form: "
"they are practicing well."

msgctxt "sn22.56:4.2"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti."
msgstr ""
"Those who practice well have a firm footing in this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:5.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ rūpaṃ abhiññāya … pe … "
"evaṃ rūpanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya, rūpassa nibbidā virāgā nirodhā "
"anupādā vimuttā te suvimuttā."
msgstr ""
"Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known form in this way—and its "
"origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation—and due "
"to disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form, are freed by "
"not grasping: they are well freed."

msgctxt "sn22.56:5.2"
msgid "Ye suvimuttā te kevalino."
msgstr "Those who are well freed are consummate ones."

msgctxt "sn22.56:5.3"
msgid "Ye kevalino vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya."
msgstr "For consummate ones, there is no cycle of rebirths to be found."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.60"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:6.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, vedanā?"
msgstr "And what is feeling?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, vedanākāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of feeling:"

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.3"
msgid ""
"cakkhusamphassajā vedanā, sotasamphassajā vedanā, ghānasamphassajā vedanā, "
"jivhāsamphassajā vedanā, kāyasamphassajā vedanā, manosamphassajā vedanā."
msgstr ""
"feeling born of contact through the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind."

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, vedanā."
msgstr "This is called feeling."

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.5"
msgid "Phassasamudayā vedanāsamudayo;"
msgstr "Feeling originates from contact."

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.6"
msgid "phassanirodhā vedanānirodho."
msgstr "When contact ceases, feeling ceases."

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.7"
msgid ""
"Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of feelings is simply this noble "
"eightfold path …"

msgctxt "sn22.56:6.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:7.1"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ vedanaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"vedanāsamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ vedanānirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"vedanānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya vedanāya nibbidāya virāgāya "
"nirodhāya paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.56:7.2"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:8.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ vedanaṃ abhiññāya … pe "
"… evaṃ vedanānirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.56:8.2"
msgid "vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:9.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, saññā?"
msgstr "And what is perception?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, saññākāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of perception:"

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.3"
msgid ""
"rūpasaññā, saddasaññā, gandhasaññā, rasasaññā, phoṭṭhabbasaññā, dhammasaññā."
msgstr "perceptions of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts."

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, saññā."
msgstr "This is called perception."

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.5"
msgid "Phassasamudayā saññāsamudayo;"
msgstr "Perception originates from contact."

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.6"
msgid "phassanirodhā saññānirodho."
msgstr "When contact ceases, perception ceases."

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.7"
msgid ""
"Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saññānirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of perceptions is simply this noble "
"eightfold path …"

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.56:9.9"
msgid "vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:10.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā?"
msgstr "And what are choices?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, cetanākāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of intention:"

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.3"
msgid ""
"rūpasañcetanā, saddasañcetanā, gandhasañcetanā, rasasañcetanā, "
"phoṭṭhabbasañcetanā, dhammasañcetanā."
msgstr ""
"intention regarding sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts."

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.4"
msgid "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā."
msgstr "These are called choices."

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.5"
msgid "Phassasamudayā saṅkhārasamudayo;"
msgstr "Choices originate from contact."

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.6"
msgid "phassanirodhā saṅkhāranirodho."
msgstr "When contact ceases, choices cease."

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.7"
msgid ""
"Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of choices is simply this noble "
"eightfold path …"

msgctxt "sn22.56:10.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.61"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:11.1"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ saṅkhāre abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"saṅkhārasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya saṅkhārānaṃ nibbidāya virāgāya "
"nirodhāya paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.56:11.2"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:12.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ saṅkhāre abhiññāya, "
"evaṃ saṅkhārasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya saṅkhārānaṃ nibbidā virāgā "
"nirodhā anupādā vimuttā, te suvimuttā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.56:12.2"
msgid "Ye suvimuttā, te kevalino."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.56:12.3"
msgid "Ye kevalino vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāya."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:13.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is consciousness?"

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.2"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, viññāṇakāyā—"
msgstr "There are these six classes of consciousness:"

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.3"
msgid ""
"cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, sotaviññāṇaṃ, ghānaviññāṇaṃ, jivhāviññāṇaṃ, kāyaviññāṇaṃ, "
"manoviññāṇaṃ."
msgstr "eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, viññāṇaṃ."
msgstr "This is called consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.5"
msgid "Nāmarūpasamudayā viññāṇasamudayo;"
msgstr "Consciousness originates from name and form."

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.6"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā viññāṇanirodho."
msgstr "When name and form cease, consciousness ceases."

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.7"
msgid ""
"Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo viññāṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The practice that leads to the cessation of consciousness is simply this "
"noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "sn22.56:13.8"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:14.1"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ viññāṇaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"viññāṇasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya viññāṇassa nibbidāya virāgāya "
"nirodhāya paṭipannā, te suppaṭipannā."
msgstr ""
"Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known consciousness in this "
"way—and its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its "
"cessation—and are practicing for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation "
"regarding consciousness: they are practicing well."

msgctxt "sn22.56:14.2"
msgid "Ye suppaṭipannā, te imasmiṃ dhammavinaye gādhanti."
msgstr ""
"Those who practice well have a firm footing in this teaching and training."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.56:15.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā evaṃ viññāṇaṃ abhiññāya, "
"evaṃ viññāṇasamudayaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ viññāṇanirodhaṃ abhiññāya, evaṃ "
"viññāṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ abhiññāya viññāṇassa nibbidā virāgā nirodhā "
"anupādā vimuttā, te suvimuttā."
msgstr ""
"Those ascetics and brahmins who have directly known consciousness in this "
"way—and its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its "
"cessation—and due to disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding "
"consciousness, are freed by not grasping: they are well freed."

msgctxt "sn22.56:15.2"
msgid "Ye suvimuttā, te kevalino."
msgstr "Those who are well freed are consummate ones."

msgctxt "sn22.56:15.3"
msgid "Ye kevalino vaṭṭaṃ tesaṃ natthi paññāpanāyā”ti."
msgstr "For consummate ones, there is no cycle of rebirths to be found.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.56:15.4"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
